Max had still been inspecting the walls of this... place under the pub. He'd tasked Moonshine and Zahir on finding out more information about whatever this place was, -they had scampered upstairs to use the computer- so now he was inspecting the structural integrity -or what was left of it- in the place. He finally lifted his head to see Rebecca, standing before the mound of rocks that had crashed down in their little fight. He frowned. She seemed... off since what happened... perhaps he should talk to her...

Becca stared at the pile of rubble, under which she knew lay the bodies of two people she had barely even had the opportunity to meet. She noticed as each person went about their respective tasks, but she couldn't find it in herself to walk away just yet. Her eyes were glued to the pile. The logical part of her knew they were both dead- she had seen the one with flames on her shoulders presumably die before she had even been buried- but the emotional part of her tried to convince her that they would be alive if she would just start digging.

She hadn't wanted to kill them. If only the man had stopped fighting her- she forced herself to take a deep breath that irritated whatever nauseating spell had been place upon her. She didn't feel good.

Max kept his distance from the others, ~~saving himself from the pain of losing them~~keeping them at an arm's length for their safety... However... Despite what he tells himself, this is ***his*** team... ~~he has to help them~~ it's his responsibility to make sure they are battle-ready at all times. So, Max approached Becca, making sure to keep his steps loud enough that she could hear him coming. Though he knew what it was like to be wrapped up in your thoughts, sometimes even that wasn't enough to break the chains of your brain. Standing across from her, far enough away that if she was spooked by him, he'd have enough time to stop her attack, he stared at the pile of rubble.

Becca quietly turned to Max. Sorrow filled her eyes. "You know... when I left my position as an EMT, I was secretly hoping I left behind the pain of death, too." Her voice wavered. "I understand that sometimes we have to stand up and protect the others, but... these two. We don't-" Becca's voice cracked, and she took a moment, "We don't even know why they were doing this. What if we made the wrong decision, interfering? What if they didn't have to die?"

Max turned to look her in the eyes. His face softened...god... he saw so much of his little sister in Becca's eyes... He didn't break eye contact, he could never with Becca, not like this. "Those answers aren't simple Becca. It will... it will never get easier to kill, no matter how many times you pull the trigger, no matter how many bodies you clean up, good, evil, a life is a life. Everyone has... reasons for what they do Becca. You never escape death-" Max let out a dry chuckle as he gazed to the ceiling "-not as a civilian, not as a soldier, not as a doctor. And while you have to move on..." Max lifted his arm, wanting to put it on her shoulder, but stopped himself. *Arm's length, Porter, come on, get that through your head,* Max thought. "...It's okay to mourn the loss of someone you never got to truly meet. And, I'm sorry you couldn't get that opportunity."

Becca let out a shaky sigh. "I know. You would think after years of seeing it, I would be somewhat less... hurt by it." A tear escaped Becca's eye without her bidding, and she quickly pulled down the sleeve of her sweater and wiped it away. She kept the sweater over her hand and gently played with the soft material, trying to ignore both her physical and mental pain. "At least, since I've been a part of this team, I know that the people I've seen die are mostly people determined to do evil, I suppose. Sometimes knowing they mean you guys harm makes it less hard. Not this time though, I guess." More tears came, and Becca rushed to wipe them away even though she knew Max could see them fall.
"There is no good guys or bad guys in this world Becca, only people. People who do things for reasons that some know and others don't." Max moved to the pile of rocks and began moving them.

A low chuckle escaped Becca unbidden. "That doesn't exactly help, Max. I'm *killing people*. I took a vow that I would *help*-" Becca sank to the ground, the nausea and dizziness finally getting to her. She buried her head in her hands, muffling her gasping breaths. She could hear the stones moving away as Max pulled on them, and couldn't decide whether she should stay and check on the two who were probably dead, or if she should try to get back to the haven.
Max paused pulling stones and kneeled in front of Becca. His hands stuttered as he forced himself to reach out place his hands on Becca's shoulders. "Becca, hey, can you look at me?"
Becca turned her head up, looking toward Max. Her vision blurred through the tears as she pressed herself slightly against Max's grounding grip.
"There we go, now, follow my lead, take a nice, deep breath in..." Max began to take exagrated breaths in, hold them, and let them out, making sure Becca followed.

Becca caught her breath slowly, clenching her hands in her sweater as she kept herself pressed against Max's hands. The tears slowed, and she fought her eyes as they tried to close. Now that she was slightly more coherent, she realized shouldn't show her exhaustion. She was fine. She knew better than to break down like this, let alone in front of her partners. Even as these thoughts ran through her head, she couldn't bring herself to pull away from the ground Max was offering.

Once Becca seemed to be mostly calm, Max pulled her into a -for him- awkward hug. He hadn't really hugged anyone, much less someone in distress in years... he would hate to mess it up. So, he made sure to stay vigilant for any body language that Becca wanted out.

The hug startled Becca. Honestly, she never took Max to be the kind to even offer a hug, so when she was pulled in, it took her off guard. She didn't hesitate to hug back though, the warmth reminding her of the kind of tender care she hadn't had the opportunity to experience since her parents- Becca shut down that train of thought, and focused on the gentle, if slightly awkward, hug. She relaxed into Max, but was cautious that she didn't lean into him too far. Even though she was happy, she didn't want to invade on his space any more than he was willing to offer.

Hugging Max was a bit like hugging a soft, firm, pillow. His clothes were extremely soft -comfort is the number one priority for Max after all- and though it's a bit awkward, his arms were sturdy and welcoming. Max held on for as long as Becca wanted, waiting for her to pull away to move.

After a while, Becca couldn't ignore the illness she still felt in her core. Something about whatever spell the man in black had put on her wasn't right, and it wasn't going away as quickly as she had hoped. As much as she didn't want to pull away from the hug she knew she so desperately wanted, she knew she had to get back to her bed in case whatever this was got any worse. Becca leaned back, looking down to the floor as she spoke. "Thank you, Max. You... you have no idea how much I needed that. As much as I would love to keep this up, though, I really don't feel well. I probably should try to get back up to my bed in the haven. Do you think you can handle..." Becca ever so slightly gestured to the rubble. She didn't think she would be able to handle seeing the bodies. At least, not right now.
Max nodded. "I'm going to take you back to your room now." His voice left no room for arguments as he stood and offered Becca a hand.
Becca didn't even have the energy to argue, taking Max's hand and pulling herself up. She pushed past the weakness she felt and walked as confidently as she could toward the rickety escalators.
Max helped her the best he could, but when it came to the stairs, he paused. "Becca, may I carry you?"

Becca hesitated. On one hand, she didn't want to be seen as weak by the others. On the other hand, though, she *really* didn't want to have a repeat experience of what happened to Moonshine when had tried to climb the steps earlier in the night. She sighed and nodded, letting herself be moved however Max felt was easiest to carry her.
Max gently lifted her bridal style, tucking her close to his chest as he climbed the escalator. To Max, it was no different from when he had to carry wounded soldiers out of the line of fire.

Becca relaxed into Max, not fighting as he carried her. She remembered the times when she had carried many of her patients this way, and the few times she had been carried this way herself. Despite her previous worry, she couldn't deny that it felt nice to be helped sometimes.

Once Max had reached the whole they had burst through -*We need a door here or something, jeez.*- he realised Becca had fallen asleep. He placed her in her bed, attempting to make her as comfortable as possible. Once he was done, he when upstairs, found(hunted) enough blood for one vitae, and collected it for when Becca woke. She'd need something to get her strength back, after all.

@Max-A-Million Let's use this as a spot for information Max has on Ian and his crew. Feel free to ask questions here as well. No hurry, I just don't want stuff getting lost in general.

Things Max would know about Ian's crew before planning an invasion: His thugs are mostly Nosferatu. This means they lack somewhat in intelligence, but make up for it in cruelty. Their Nightmare ability allows them to prey on others fears and cause them to shut down. Their weapons are mostly cheap Russian imports (Ian struggled for a long time to get weapons, then found a supplier in the Ukraine). This means that they only fire in full auto. It also means they're unreliable. In game terms, this means they don't reroll 10s and 1s subtract from successes.

Beyond the thugs, there are a handful of the usual sycophants. They range in types, but Max has never seen any of them in action. Also, after the team took out Ian's seneschal, he was replaced. The new one is a woman. Max doesn't know much about her, but she seems efficient.
If Max would look into the new seneschal or interact with her in any way, let me know what you need
